Score: 1.0
Reasoning: The implementation correctly finds the minimal number of the form 2^k - 1 (all set bits) that is >= n by using n.bit_length() and checking (1<<bits)-1, falling back to the next bit length when necessary. It handles edge cases (e.g., n already all ones, n=1) and meets the problem constraints, so it will pass all test cases.
